OL,3,CHow my father's fear triggered an
OL,4,Cinvestigation into last summer's riots
OL,6,FThe children spoke of being scared
OL,7,Fthat they might be attacked, while the
OL,8,Fadults lived in fear and unable to
OL,9,Faccept that this felt like home
OL,10,Fanymore.
OL,12,FThis interview for me was the moment I
OL,13,Fdecided to explore this issue of how
OL,14,Fwe got to this place, where the
OL,15,Fcountry was so seemingly divided.
OL,17,FA country where immigrants were seen
OL,18,Fas "freeloaders" and anyone who wanted
OL,19,Fto control our borders as "racists".
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/16
