OL,3,CHow my father's fear triggered an
OL,4,Cinvestigation into last summer's riots
OL,6,FEric is now awaiting his fate in this
OL,7,Fcountry. He's been left in limbo
OL,8,Funable to get a job and start a new
OL,9,Flife, while he waits for his asylum
OL,10,Fclaim to be processed, Eric is housed
OL,11,Fin a hotel. In 2024 he was in
OL,12,FTamworth, a place that became a target
OL,13,Fduring the protests.
OL,15,FHe told me how he watched the angry
OL,16,Fmob shouting and trying to break in.
OL,17,FHe said that while hiding inside he
OL,18,Fencouraged all the others to pray to
OL,19,Ftheir God, because he was scared they
OL,20,Fwould all be killed.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G13/16
